    <item>
      <title>How does it work?</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/how-eci-works/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/how-eci-works/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Docker implements Enhanced Container Isolation by using the &#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://github.com/nestybox/sysbox&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Sysbox&#xA;container runtime&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Sysbox is a fork of the&#xA;standard OCI runc runtime that was modified to enhance standard container isolation and&#xA;workloads. For more details see &#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;#under-the-hood&#34;&gt;Under the hood&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Key features and benefits</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/features-benefits/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/features-benefits/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34; scroll-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;linux-user-namespace-on-all-containers&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;#linux-user-namespace-on-all-containers&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Linux user namespace on all containers&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;With Enhanced Container Isolation, all user containers leverage the &#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man7/user_namespaces.7.html&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Linux user namespace&lt;span class=&#34;pl-1 icon-svg icon-sm&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M180-120q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-600q0-24 18-42t42-18h249q12.75 0 21.38 8.68 8.62 8.67 8.62 21.5 0 12.82-8.62 21.32-8.63 8.5-21.38 8.5H180v600h600v-249q0-12.75 8.68-21.38 8.67-8.62 21.5-8.62 12.82 0 21.32 8.62 8.5 8.63 8.5 21.38v249q0 24-18 42t-42 18H180Zm600-617L403-360q-9 9-21 8.5t-21-9.5q-9-9-9-21t9-21l377-377H549q-12.75 0-21.37-8.68-8.63-8.67-8.63-21.5 0-12.82 8.63-21.32 8.62-8.5 21.37-8.5h261q12.75 0 21.38 8.62Q840-822.75 840-810v261q0 12.75-8.68 21.37-8.67 8.63-21.5 8.63-12.82 0-21.32-8.63-8.5-8.62-8.5-21.37v-188Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;for extra isolation. This means that the root user in the container maps to an unprivileged&#xA;user in the Docker Desktop Linux VM.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Advanced configuration options for ECI</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/config/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/config/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34; scroll-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;docker-socket-mount-permissions&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;#docker-socket-mount-permissions&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Docker socket mount permissions&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;By default, when Enhanced Container Isolation (ECI) is enabled, Docker Desktop does not allow bind-mounting the&#xA;Docker Engine socket into containers:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div data-pagefind-ignore class=&#34;scroll-mt-20&#34; x-data x-ref=&#34;root&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;group relative&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;button x-data=&#34;{ code: &#39;&#39;, copying: false }&#34;&#xA;      class=&#34;absolute right-3 top-3 z-10 text-gray-light-300 dark:text-gray-dark-600&#34; title=&#34;copy&#34; @click=&#34;window.navigator.clipboard.writeText(atob(code).replaceAll(/^[\$&gt;]\s+/gm, &#39;&#39;));&#xA;      copying = true;&#xA;      setTimeout(() =&gt; copying = false, 2000);&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : !copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M300-200q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-560q0-24 18-42t42-18h440q24 0 42 18t18 42v560q0 24-18 42t-42 18H300ZM180-80q-24 0-42-18t-18-42v-590q0-13 8.5-21.5T150-760q13 0 21.5 8.5T180-730v590h470q13 0 21.5 8.5T680-110q0 13-8.5 21.5T650-80H180Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span :class=&#34;{ &#39;group-hover:block&#39; : copying }&#34; class=&#34;icon-svg hidden&#34;&gt;&lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;m421-389-98-98q-9-9-22-9t-23 10q-9 9-9 22t9 22l122 123q9 9 21 9t21-9l239-239q10-10 10-23t-10-23q-10-9-23.5-8.5T635-603L421-389Zm59 309q-82 0-155-31.5t-127.5-86Q143-252 111.5-325T80-480q0-83 31.5-156t86-127Q252-817 325-848.5T480-880q83 0 156 31.5T763-763q54 54 85.5 127T880-480q0 82-31.5 155T763-197.5q-54 54.5-127 86T480-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/button&gt;&#xA;     &#xA;    &lt;div class=&#34;syntax-light dark:syntax-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-console&#34; data-lang=&#34;console&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;gp&#34;&gt;$&lt;/span&gt; docker run -it --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock docker:cli&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;go&#34;&gt;docker: Error response from daemon: enhanced container isolation: docker socket mount denied for container with image &amp;#34;docker.io/library/docker&amp;#34;; image is not in the allowed list; if you wish to allow it, configure the docker socket image list in the Docker Desktop settings.&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This prevents malicious containers from gaining access to the Docker Engine, as&#xA;such access could allow them to perform supply chain attacks. For example, build and&#xA;push malicious images into the organization&#39;s repositories or similar.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Enhanced Container Isolation FAQs</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/faq/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/faq/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 class=&#34; scroll-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;do-i-need-to-change-the-way-i-use-docker-when-eci-is-switched-on&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;#do-i-need-to-change-the-way-i-use-docker-when-eci-is-switched-on&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Do I need to change the way I use Docker when ECI is switched on?&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;No, you can continue to use Docker as usual. ECI works under the covers by&#xA;creating a more secure container.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34; scroll-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;do-all-container-workloads-work-well-with-eci&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;#do-all-container-workloads-work-well-with-eci&#34;&gt;&#xA;    Do all container workloads work well with ECI?&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The great majority of container workloads run fine with ECI enabled, but a few&#xA;do not (yet). For the few workloads that don&#39;t yet work with Enhanced Container&#xA;Isolation, Docker is continuing to improve the feature to reduce this to a&#xA;minimum.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Limitations</title>
      <link>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/limitations/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://docker.qubitpi.org/security/for-admins/hardened-desktop/enhanced-container-isolation/limitations/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 class=&#34; scroll-mt-20&#34; id=&#34;eci-support-for-wsl&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;text-black dark:text-white no-underline hover:underline&#34; href=&#34;#eci-support-for-wsl&#34;&gt;&#xA;    ECI support for WSL&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &lt;blockquote&#xA;    &#xA;    class=&#34;px-4 border-l-4 border-blue-light dark:border-blue-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;p class=&#34;flex gap-2 items-center text-blue-light dark:text-blue-dark&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;span class=&#34;icon-svg pb-1&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;svg xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34; width=&#34;48&#34; height=&#34;48&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 -960 960 960&#34;&gt;&lt;path d=&#34;M483.18-280q12.82 0 21.32-8.63 8.5-8.62 8.5-21.37v-180q0-12.75-8.68-21.38-8.67-8.62-21.5-8.62-12.82 0-21.32 8.62-8.5 8.63-8.5 21.38v180q0 12.75 8.68 21.37 8.67 8.63 21.5 8.63Zm-3.2-314q14.02 0 23.52-9.2T513-626q0-14.45-9.48-24.22-9.48-9.78-23.5-9.78t-23.52 9.78Q447-640.45 447-626q0 13.6 9.48 22.8 9.48 9.2 23.5 9.2Zm.29 514q-82.74 0-155.5-31.5Q252-143 197.5-197.5t-86-127.34Q80-397.68 80-480.5t31.5-155.66Q143-709 197.5-763t127.34-85.5Q397.68-880 480.5-880t155.66 31.5Q709-817 763-763t85.5 127Q880-563 880-480.27q0 82.74-31.5 155.5Q817-252 763-197.68q-54 54.31-127 86Q563-80 480.27-80Z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&#xA;      &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;      &lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/p&gt;&#xA;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Docker Desktop requires WSL 2 version 1.1.3.0 or later. To get the current&#xA;version of WSL on your host, type &lt;code&gt;wsl --version&lt;/code&gt;. If the command fails or if&#xA;it returns a version number prior to 1.1.3.0, update WSL to the latest version&#xA;by typing &lt;code&gt;wsl --update&lt;/code&gt; in a Windows command or PowerShell terminal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
